---
layout: base.njk
---
<main id="top">
  <section class="hero"><div class="wrap hero-grid">
    <div>
      <span class="kicker label"><span class="dot"></span>Where next &middot; travel, sorted</span>
      <h1>Every city, one&nbsp;clear <em>next stop.</em></h1>
      <p class="lead">WHRNXT turns a place you've never been into a plan you can actually follow — sights, food, and transit for 2,300+ cities, with a trip you can share in a tap.</p>
      <div class="cta-row">
        <a class="btn btn-signal" href="{{ site.appUrl }}">Open the app &#9656;</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="#plan">See how it works</a>
      </div>
      <div class="trust">
        <span><b>Free</b> to use</span>
        <span><b>No login</b> needed</span>
        <span><b>Works offline</b></span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="demo" id="demo">
      <div class="demo-bar">
        <span class="demo-status mono" id="demo-mode"><span class="demo-dot"></span>BROWSING MODE &mdash; location set as Rome, Italy.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="demo-screen">
        <iframe
          id="demo-frame"
          class="demo-frame"
          title="WHRNXT app, live demo browsing New York"
          src="{{ site.appUrl }}/?embed=1&amp;city=rome"
          loading="lazy"
          allow="geolocation"
          referrerpolicy="origin"></iframe>
      </div>
      <div class="demo-foot">
        <button class="btn btn-signal" id="demo-locate" type="button">Use my location &#9656;</button>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="{{ site.appUrl }}">Open full app</a>
      </div>
      <p class="demo-fine" id="demo-fine">Browsing Rome &mdash; no location needed. Pick any city inside, or switch to where you actually are.</p>
    </div>
  </div></section>

  <div class="ticker" aria-hidden="true"><div class="ticker-in">
    <span><b>2,300+</b> cities</span><span><b>60,000+</b> places</span><span>PARIS</span><span>TOKYO</span><span>NANTUCKET</span><span><b>Works offline</b></span><span>CAPE TOWN</span><span>MOAB</span><span>KYOTO</span><span><b>No login</b></span><span>TELLURIDE</span><span>LISBON</span><span><b>Free</b></span>
    <span><b>2,300+</b> cities</span><span><b>60,000+</b> places</span><span>PARIS</span><span>TOKYO</span><span>NANTUCKET</span><span><b>Works offline</b></span><span>CAPE TOWN</span><span>MOAB</span><span>KYOTO</span><span><b>No login</b></span><span>TELLURIDE</span><span>LISBON</span><span><b>Free</b></span>
  </div></div>

  <section class="block" id="find"><div class="wrap">
    <div class="sec-head">
      <span class="label">What it does</span>
      <h2>Get your bearings anywhere — then keep moving.</h2>
      <p>WHRNXT isn't a list of links. It's a hand-picked guide to what's worth your time in each place, measured from wherever you're standing.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feat">
      <div class="card">
        <span class="label">Find</span>
        <svg class="pin" width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path fill="currentColor" d="M12 2a7 7 0 0 0-7 7c0 5 7 13 7 13s7-8 7-13a7 7 0 0 0-7-7Zm0 9.5A2.5 2.5 0 1 1 12 6.5a2.5 2.5 0 0 1 0 5Z"/></svg>
        <h3>Sights &amp; food for 2,300+ cities</h3>
        <p>From Tokyo to a small airport town, browse the places actually worth visiting — sorted by distance, with the real transit hubs to reach them. Preview any city without turning on location.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card" id="plan">
        <span class="label">Plan</span>
        <svg class="pin" width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path fill="currentColor" d="M4 5h16v2H4Zm0 6h10v2H4Zm0 6h16v2H4Z"/></svg>
        <h3>A trip that plans the walking for you</h3>
        <p>Add your stops and WHRNXT chains them into the shortest sensible day. Then it hands you a share link — friends open the exact plan, no account and no app-store detour.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card" id="transit">
        <span class="label">Transit</span>
        <svg class="pin" width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path fill="currentColor" d="M12 2c-4 0-8 .5-8 4v9.5A2.5 2.5 0 0 0 6.5 18L5 19.5V20h2l2-2h6l2 2h2v-.5L17.5 18A2.5 2.5 0 0 0 20 15.5V6c0-3.5-4-4-8-4ZM7.5 17A1.5 1.5 0 1 1 9 15.5 1.5 1.5 0 0 1 7.5 17Zm9 0a1.5 1.5 0 1 1 1.5-1.5 1.5 1.5 0 0 1-1.5 1.5ZM18 11H6V6h12Z"/></svg>
        <h3>Airports &amp; stations, sorted</h3>
        <p>Every city shows its real transit. Tap "nearby cities' transit" and WHRNXT pulls in the airports and stations within reach — deduped and nearest-first, so you see one Newark, not eighteen.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <span class="label">Offline</span>
        <svg class="pin" width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path fill="currentColor" d="M12 3a9 9 0 1 0 9 9 9 9 0 0 0-9-9Zm6.7 7H14.4A9.9 9.9 0 0 0 12.9 5.1 7 7 0 0 1 18.7 10ZM12 5a9.9 9.9 0 0 1 1.5 5h-3A9.9 9.9 0 0 1 12 5ZM5.3 10a7 7 0 0 1 4.1-4.4A11.7 11.7 0 0 0 8 10Zm0 4H8a11.7 11.7 0 0 0 1.4 4.4A7 7 0 0 1 5.3 14ZM12 19a9.9 9.9 0 0 1-1.5-3.5h3A9.9 9.9 0 0 1 12 19Zm-1.9-5.5a13 13 0 0 1 0-3h3.8a13 13 0 0 1 0 3Zm4.5 3.9A11.7 11.7 0 0 0 16 14h2.7a7 7 0 0 1-4.1 4.4Z"/></svg>
        <h3>Works with no signal</h3>
        <p>WHRNXT runs in your browser and keeps working on the plane, underground, or abroad without data. Nothing to install, no sign-up, and it's free.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="block" id="share" style="padding-top:0"><div class="wrap"><div class="split">
    <div class="panel-lg">
      <span class="label">Community</span>
      <h2>Made a good trip? Share it.</h2>
      <p>Post a WHRNXT share link (or any trip link). No account needed.</p>
      <form id="trip-form" novalidate>
        <p hidden><label>Leave blank: <input name="website" tabindex="-1" autocomplete="off"></label></p>
        <label class="f" for="t-title">Trip title</label>
        <input id="t-title" name="title" placeholder="A long weekend in Lisbon" required>
        <div class="form-row">
          <div><label class="f" for="t-cities">Cities</label><input id="t-cities" name="cities" placeholder="Lisbon, Sintra"></div>
          <div><label class="f" for="t-link">Share link</label><input id="t-link" name="link" type="url" placeholder="https://app.whrnxt.net/?i=…" required></div>
        </div>
        <button class="btn btn-signal" type="submit" id="trip-submit" style="align-self:flex-start;margin-top:6px">Post trip &#9656;</button>
      </form>
      <p class="fine" id="trip-msg">Your trip is held for review and goes live once approved &mdash; no spam, no junk links.</p>
      <a class="browse" href="/trips/">Browse shared trips &#9656;</a>
    </div>
    <div class="panel-lg">
      <span class="label">How to use it</span>
      <h2>Four modes, one app.</h2>
      <p>WHRNXT works differently depending on what you're doing — standing somewhere, planning ahead, or following a route you already built. Pick a mode to see how it works.</p>

      <div class="modes">
        <div class="mode-tabs" role="tablist" aria-label="App modes">
          <button class="mode-tab is-on" role="tab" aria-selected="true"  aria-controls="mode-current"  id="tab-current"  data-mode="current">Current</button>
          <button class="mode-tab"       role="tab" aria-selected="false" aria-controls="mode-browsing" id="tab-browsing" data-mode="browsing">Browsing</button>
          <button class="mode-tab"       role="tab" aria-selected="false" aria-controls="mode-planning" id="tab-planning" data-mode="planning">Trip planner</button>
          <button class="mode-tab"       role="tab" aria-selected="false" aria-controls="mode-saved"    id="tab-saved"    data-mode="saved">Saved</button>
        </div>

        <div class="mode-panel" role="tabpanel" id="mode-current" aria-labelledby="tab-current">
          <p class="mode-why">For when you're already somewhere and want to know what's around you.</p>
          <p>Tap <strong>Current</strong> at the top so WHRNXT uses your GPS. Move between the <strong>Sights</strong>, <strong>Events</strong>, <strong>Food</strong>, and <strong>Transit</strong> tabs — everything is listed nearest-first. Tap a place for details, directions, or to book a ride, and swipe left/right inside it to flip through the list. In <strong>Settings</strong>, <strong>Show nearby within</strong> limits the list to a distance you choose.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="mode-panel" role="tabpanel" id="mode-browsing" aria-labelledby="tab-browsing" hidden>
          <p class="mode-why">For sizing up a city you haven't reached yet — no location needed.</p>
          <p>Tap the <strong>Current</strong> button to switch to <strong>Browsing</strong>, then pick any city. You'll see its places as if you were standing in the middle of it, with distances measured from the city center. Tap <strong>Browsing</strong> again to snap back to where you really are. This is the mode running in the demo above.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="mode-panel" role="tabpanel" id="mode-planning" aria-labelledby="tab-planning" hidden>
          <p class="mode-why">For turning a pile of places into a day you can actually walk.</p>
          <p>Tap the <strong>Planning</strong> tab, then <strong>New itinerary</strong>. Use <strong>Add Day</strong> to pick that day's city, then <strong>Add stops</strong> — the list re-sorts by distance from your last stop, so the route builds itself. Tap the <strong>⚓ anchor</strong> to lock a stop in place and <strong>✨ Optimize route</strong> to arrange the rest around it. Then <strong>▶ Launch day</strong> to follow it live, or <strong>Share</strong> to send it to someone as a link.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="mode-panel" role="tabpanel" id="mode-saved" aria-labelledby="tab-saved" hidden>
          <p class="mode-why">For the places you want to keep, rename, or annotate for yourself.</p>
          <p>Tap the <strong>★</strong> on any place to save it, and find everything you've starred in the <strong>★</strong> tab. Open a place and tap <strong>✏️</strong> to give it your own name ("Mom's favorite pizza"), or jot a private note below the address ("gate code 1234") — both stay on your device and are never shared. The <strong>📍</strong> button adds your own spots: pin exactly where you're standing, or search an address and drag the pin.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div style="margin-top:22px" class="trust"><span><span class="mono" style="color:var(--go)">&#9679;</span> Web app live now</span><span><b>iOS &amp; Android</b> next</span></div>
    </div>
  </div></div></section>
</main>

{% raw %}<script>
// Trip submission → held as pending on the server until a human approves it.
(function(){
  var API = {% endraw %}{{ site.apiUrl | dump | safe }}{% raw %};
  var form = document.getElementById('trip-form');
  var msg  = document.getElementById('trip-msg');
  var btn  = document.getElementById('trip-submit');
  if(!form) return;

  form.addEventListener('submit', function(e){
    e.preventDefault();
    var title = form.title.value.trim();
    var link  = form.link.value.trim();
    if(!title || !link){ msg.textContent = 'A title and a share link are both needed.'; return; }
    btn.disabled = true;
    var was = btn.textContent;
    btn.textContent = 'Posting…';
    fetch(API + '/api/trips', {
      method: 'POST',
      headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
      body: JSON.stringify({
        title: title,
        cities: form.cities.value.trim(),
        link: link,
        website: form.website.value,   // honeypot
      }),
    })
    .then(function(r){ return r.json().then(function(d){ return { ok: r.ok, d: d }; }); })
    .then(function(res){
      if(!res.ok){
        var why = res.d && res.d.error === 'bad_link'
          ? 'That link does not look like a valid https link.'
          : res.d && res.d.error === 'rate_limited'
            ? 'That is a lot of trips at once — try again in a few minutes.'
            : 'Something went wrong posting that. Please try again.';
        msg.textContent = why;
        btn.disabled = false; btn.textContent = was;
        return;
      }
      form.reset();
      form.style.display = 'none';
      msg.textContent = 'Thanks — your trip is in the queue. It appears on the Shared trips page once a human approves it.';
    })
    .catch(function(){
      msg.textContent = 'Could not reach the server. Please try again shortly.';
      btn.disabled = false; btn.textContent = was;
    });
  });
})();

(function(){
  var frame  = document.getElementById('demo-frame');
  var locate = document.getElementById('demo-locate');
  var mode   = document.getElementById('demo-mode');
  var fine   = document.getElementById('demo-fine');
  if(!frame || !locate) return;

  var APP_ORIGIN = new URL(frame.src).origin;

  function send(type){
    if(frame.contentWindow) frame.contentWindow.postMessage({type:type}, APP_ORIGIN);
  }

  // Rebuild the status line as nodes — the city name crosses a frame boundary,
  // so it goes in as text, never as markup.
  function setMode(text){
    mode.textContent = '';
    var dot = document.createElement('span');
    dot.className = 'demo-dot';
    mode.appendChild(dot);
    mode.appendChild(document.createTextNode(text));
  }

  locate.addEventListener('click', function(){
    if(locate.dataset.mode === 'current'){ send('whrnxt:browse'); return; }
    // The iframe carries allow="geolocation", so the app's own request prompts here.
    send('whrnxt:use-location');
    locate.textContent = 'Locating…';
    locate.disabled = true;
  });

  // The app reports its mode back so the button reflects what's actually on screen.
  window.addEventListener('message', function(e){
    if(e.origin !== APP_ORIGIN) return;
    var d = e.data;
    if(!d || d.type !== 'whrnxt:mode') return;
    locate.disabled = false;
    if(d.browseMode === 'current'){
      locate.dataset.mode = 'current';
      locate.textContent = 'Back to browsing ▸';
      setMode('CURRENT MODE — using your real location.');
      fine.textContent = 'Showing places near you. Switch back to browse any other city.';
    } else {
      locate.dataset.mode = 'browse';
      locate.textContent = 'Use my location ▸';
      var city = d.cityName || 'Rome, Italy';
      setMode('BROWSING MODE — location set as ' + city + '.');
      fine.textContent = 'Browsing ' + city + ' — no location needed. Pick any city inside, or switch to where you actually are.';
    }
  });
})();

// How-to mode carousel
(function(){
  var tabs = Array.prototype.slice.call(document.querySelectorAll('.mode-tab'));
  if(!tabs.length) return;
  function show(tab){
    tabs.forEach(function(t){
      var on = t === tab;
      t.classList.toggle('is-on', on);
      t.setAttribute('aria-selected', on ? 'true' : 'false');
      document.getElementById(t.getAttribute('aria-controls')).hidden = !on;
    });
  }
  tabs.forEach(function(t){
    t.addEventListener('click', function(){ show(t); });
    t.addEventListener('keydown', function(e){
      var i = tabs.indexOf(t), n = null;
      if(e.key === 'ArrowRight') n = tabs[(i + 1) % tabs.length];
      else if(e.key === 'ArrowLeft') n = tabs[(i - 1 + tabs.length) % tabs.length];
      if(n){ e.preventDefault(); show(n); n.focus(); }
    });
  });
})();
</script>{% endraw %}
